        <h1 class ="new" style="line-height:1.6; text-align:left; margin-left:-155px; margin-right:150px; font-weight: normal;">Hello! Welcome to the reducing tutorial, a step by step process meant to show you how equivalent fractions work! First, you should type in the greatest common factor for the numerator and denominator, that is, what is the largest number that can divide both the numerator and the denominator. After that, simply divide the numerator and the denominator by that number, and get the reduced fraction! After you type in each of your submissions, don't forget to press the "Enter" button! Try it a few times, then when you get the hang of it, move onto the games!</h1>
